# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: benlib: encoding-table data errors
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* TODO [#B] benlib: fix encoding-table data errors  :benlib:data:

Severity: *high* (silent wrong conversions) — these are data bugs, not crashes:
affected characters simply fail to convert or have no ASCII approximation.

benlib keys every encoding to a PostScript-style glyph *char-name* (e.g.
="hyphen"=, ="asterisk"=). A typo or mismatched name in any table silently
breaks conversion and approximation for that code point.

** Findings

*** [high] Missing comma merges two entries (approxim.c:352)
=  { "minus"               "-" },=
Adjacent string literals concatenate, so this is =​{ "minus-", 0 }=: there is
now *no* ="minus"= approximation, and a bogus ="minus-"= key is injected.
Fix: =  { "minus",               "-" },=

*** [high] Same code point, different char-name across tables — =-= won't convert
- ASCII 0x2D = ="hyphen"= (encascii.c:46) vs ISO-Latin-1 0x2D = ="minus"= (encisla1.c:76).
- =*= is ="star"= in the Honeywell/IBM/Univac/EBCDIC tables (ench2bcd.c:75,
  ench6bcd.c:75, encibbcd.c:75, encebcdi.c:123, encunifd.c:72) but ="asterisk"=
  in ASCII/PostScript/approxim.
Because conversion is name→name, =-= and =*= fail to cross these encodings and
have no approximation. Fix: pick one canonical name per code point
(suggest ="hyphen"= and ="asterisk"=) and use it everywhere.

*** [medium] char-name typos (non-existent names → never convert)
- =encebcdi.c:159= ="onequater"= → ="onequarter"=.
- =encibbcd.c:58=  ="coma"=       → ="comma"=.
- =ench6bcd.c:89=  ="hypen"=      → ="hyphen"= (comment already flags it as a dup of 0x2A).

*** [medium] EBCDIC 0x79 mapped to ="cent"= (encebcdi.c:152)
0x4A is already ¢; standard EBCDIC 0x79 is the grave accent =`=. The duplicate
loses the backtick. Verify against the intended EBCDIC variant and fix.

*** [low] Suspicious / duplicate entries to verify
- =approxim.c:249-250= duplicate key ="dblrightdbldownbar"= (second unreachable).
- =encmsdos.c:158,155= 0x7F→="Delta"=, 0x7C→="bar"= (comment: "actually
  brokenbar"); CP437 0x7F is a house/⌂ glyph. Verify against CP437.
- =enctypes.h:35-36= ="BenStringP .charName;"= is not valid C (stray dot); it is
  shadowed by Bencoding.h today but will not compile if ever included directly.
  Delete or fix.

** Note (NOT bugs — internally consistent despite looking misspelled)
="logicalnotmirored"= (encmsdos.c:200 + approxim.c:346) and
="intergraltp"/"intergralbt"= (encmsdos.c:275-276 + approxim.c:326-327) are
misspelled but *consistently*, so they convert fine. Fixing the spelling means
fixing both sites together. The =encebcdi.c:207 "/* 80 */"= row comment is
mislabelled (it is 0xB0) but the data order is correct — comment-only.

** Plan
1. Add the missing comma (approxim.c:352).
2. Canonicalise ="hyphen"= and ="asterisk"= across all tables.
3. Fix the four typos; verify EBCDIC 0x79 and the MSDOS/CP437 entries.
4. Add a test that every char-name used in any =enc*.c= table exists as a key in
   =approxim.c= (and ideally in ASCII), to catch this whole class automatically.
